# 🚗 Ride-Sharing Analytics & Driver Performance

## End-to-End Data Engineering Pipeline using PySpark & Databricks Delta Lake

---

# 📖 Project Overview

The **Ride-Sharing Analytics & Driver Performance** project is a robust data engineering pipeline designed to process large volumes of operational data from ride-sharing platforms. Built using **PySpark** and **Databricks Delta Lake**, the project strictly follows the **Medallion Architecture (Bronze → Silver → Gold)**.

The entire pipeline is streamlined into a single, comprehensive Databricks notebook. It ingests raw driver and trip data, performs data cleaning and broadcast joins to enrich the dataset, and ultimately generates high-value, business-ready analytical insights.

This project demonstrates core Data Engineering concepts including distributed data processing, handling null and invalid records, PySpark optimizations (Broadcast Joins), advanced analytics using Window Functions, and Delta table management.

---

# 🎯 Project Objectives

* Build a structured data engineering pipeline using PySpark and Databricks.
* Implement the Medallion Architecture (Bronze, Silver, Gold) in a unified workflow.
* Track ride and driver activity across the platform.
* Analyze cancellations and trip delays.
* Identify high-demand pickup locations for fleet optimization.
* Evaluate driver performance and rank them by revenue generation.
* Validate data consistency across all processing layers.
* Apply Spark optimization techniques to ensure scalable data processing.

